## 4. Key Design Decisions & Rationale

| Decision | Why |
|----------|-----|
| **Polygon instead of Ethereum mainnet** | 100x cheaper gas, <2 sec finality, still decentralized. Users feel instant payouts. |
| **Stripe + Web3 dual payment** | 60% of US devs don't have crypto wallets yet; Stripe reaches everyone. |
| **Weekly (not daily) payouts** | Daily would burn on fees; weekly batches reduce cost, still fast for motivation. |
| **Codex 6-metric scoring** | 6 gates = sufficient filtering without over-optimization. 1-2 gates = spam; 10+ gates = analysis paralysis. |
| **Open quests + seeded templates** | Founder posts idea, system auto-fractures into sub-quests; lowers barrier to entry vs. "design everything yourself". |
| **Equity vesting (4yr, 1yr cliff)** | Industry standard; incentivizes long-term contributor retention; cliff prevents churn early. |
| **Product NFT (non-transferable)** | Proves ownership on-chain without creating secondary market speculation. |
| **Seasonal themes** | Keeps engagement fresh; guides contributor focus; creates urgency ("only Q1 for Light-themed quests"). |

